title: PPPP’s Bhadurdur Khan Dahri wins PS- 39 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP), Bhadurdur Khan Dahri has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-39, Shaheed Banazirabad-4, by securing 69,876 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Arif Niaz Arain of Grand Democratic Alliance, who bagged votes 15,015.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 46.41 %.
